org.apache.james.protocols.smtp

Class SMTPProtocolHandlerChain

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.james.protocols.api.handler.AbstractProtocolHandlerChain
      • org.apache.james.protocols.api.handler.ProtocolHandlerChainImpl
        • org.apache.james.protocols.smtp.SMTPProtocolHandlerChain
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<ProtocolHandler>, Collection<ProtocolHandler>, List<ProtocolHandler>, ProtocolHandlerChain
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LMTPProtocolHandlerChain

    public class SMTPProtocolHandlerChain
extends ProtocolHandlerChainImpl
    This ProtocolHandlerChain implementation add all needed handlers to the chain to act as full blown SMTPServer. By default messages will just get rejected after the DATA command.
